                            <comment id="54209" author="rjrjr@google.com" created="Thu, 3 Jun 2010 08:29:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note the existing roo logging command. Do we honor it? Parallel it? gwt log? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54730" author="rjrjr@google.com" created="Wed, 16 Jun 2010 07:48:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Decoupling this from user action tracking, which may or may not make 2.1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57585" author="rjrjr@google.com" created="Thu, 2 Sep 2010 18:56:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In dev mode, when I hit this log line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;      public void onUncaughtException(Throwable e) &lt;/p&gt;
{
        Window.alert(&quot;Error: &quot; + e.getMessage());
        log.log(Level.SEVERE, e.getMessage(), e);
      }

&lt;p&gt;I see only this in my terminal window, even though I&apos;m passing in the throwable e:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ERROR&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; SEVERE: Client Side Logger: com.springsource.extrack.gwt.scaffold.Scaffold Message: One or more exceptions caught, see full set in UmbrellaException#getCauses&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note the lack of a stack trace. The dev mode console, on the other hand, prints it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="57858" author="cramsdale" created="Thu, 9 Sep 2010 12:19:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking this as Minor...we need to make sure we flesh it out, with an eye towards App Engine.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
